content:
I'm running on a Macbook Pro M1, with code that can run just fine when using cargo run. Though if I run cargo test, change any line and run again, it gets SIGKILL immediately until I run cargo clean again. cargo run works as usual regardless.
Any ideas why this could happen? I've made sure rustc, rustup, cargo, and my terminal is running with arm64 and Xcode command tools is the latest version.
